<isis lang="en">

    <svcsubproc>
        <title>Range Mainshaft Assembly</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Secure the output shaft in a vise with the mainshaft quill up (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13018l0">Figure 210</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13018l0" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13018l0" filename="../figg13/G13018L0.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 209. Secure Output Shaft in Vise</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If necessary, press the bushing in the rear bore of the range mainshaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13018l1">inset, Figure 211</hotlnk>) and install the mainshaft in position on the
                quill.
            </para>
            <figure id="f13018l1" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13018l1" filename="../figg13/G13018L1.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 210. Press Bushing in Rear Bore of Range Mainshaft and Install Mainshaft</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the bearings in the front bore of the range mainshaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13018l2">Figure 212</hotlnk>). Use a small flanged-end driver to properly seat bearing
                in the bore on the mainshaft quill.
            </para>
            <figure id="f13018l2" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13018l2" filename="../figg13/G13018L2.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 211. Install Bearings in Front Bore of Range Mainshaft</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the "C" ring in the groove of the mainshaft quill to retain bearing (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13018l3">Figure 213</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13018l3" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13018l3" filename="../figg13/G13018L3.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 212. Install "C" Ring in Groove of Mainshaft Quill</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcsubproc>
